{% comment %}
  Home page colophon hero. Optional:
  - vt_style: inline style for view transitions (e.g. view-transition-name: home)
{% endcomment %}

{% styles "components/home-hero" %}

<header role="banner" class="HomeHero" aria-labelledby="home-hero-name">
  <div class="HomeHero__inner">
    <p class="HomeHero__greeting">Hello there, I’m <span title="This is a perfectly legitimate use case for the em dash; it’s not AI." class="HomeHero__emdash">—</span></p>

    {% render "title.liquid", title: "Kitty Giraudel." %}

    <p class="HomeHero__line HomeHero__line--roles">
      Frontend developer · Engineering leader · Published author
    </p>

    <div class="HomeHero__bio">
      {% renderTemplate "md" %}
      I’m a frontend developer and engineering leader based in Berlin, with nearly 15 years of experience. I focus on software excellence, accessibility, diversity and inclusion. In recent years, I have led engineering teams at [N26](https://n26.com), [Gorillas](<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gorillas_(company)>), [cofenster](https://cofenster.com/), and [Scilife](https://scilife.io), and I am now doing frontend at [Duna](https://duna.com). Aside of my primary activity, I write about the web on this blog, and have been doing so since 2012.

      Read more [about me](/about/), my [AI policy](/ai-policy/), and [my accessibility statement](/accessibility-statement/).
      {% endrenderTemplate %}
    </div>

    <p class="HomeHero__line HomeHero__line--focus">
      Accessibility · Diversity & Inclusion · Authenticity
    </p>
  </div>
</header>
